Barrett M107A1 is a semi-automatic rifle chambered in .50 BMG. Barrett touts that the M107A1 is “a lighter yet stronger” version of the original 82A1/M107. olymer bi-pod. Like the 82A1, a rifle praised for its lightweight, low recoil, dependability and accuracy, the M107A1 has a straight-forward design.

The M107A1 has a 29-inch fluted barrel, which puts the overall length of 57 inches, and it weighs 30.9 pounds. However, a shorter barreled version is also available.

The rifle is in very good shape and has only had less than 500 rounds fired through it. Despite its low use, I have disassembled it and cleaned it thoroughly, so it's almost brand new. I was able to get a grouping the size of a half dollar coin at 100 yards once the scope was sighted in while shooting very casually and rapidly. 92SB (92S-1)[edit]
The extremely rare 92SB, Initially called the 92S-1, was specifically designed for the USAF (US Air Force) trials (which it won), the model name officially adopted was the 92SB. It included the changes of the 92S, added a firing pin block (thus the addition of the "B" to the name), and relocated the magazine release catch from the bottom of the grip to the lower bottom of the trigger guard. A compact version with a shortened barrel and slide and 13-round magazine capacity known as the 92SB Compact was manufactured from 1981 to 1991
